    "body": "@zcbenz Is there a native API that can be provided in the `screen` module then to do this test at a native level.\n\nSomething like  `display.containsPoint(point)`\n\nUsage would be something like\n\n``` js\nimport { screen } from 'electron';\n\nconst point = [-100, 27];\n\nlet validPoint = false;\nscreen.getAllDisplays().forEach((display) => {\n    validPoint = validPoint || display.containsPoint(point);\n});\n```\n\nOn a side note aswell\n\n> The APIs are just returning the values given by OS X\n\nDoes that mean OS X is bugged ðŸ˜– \n"
